            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes. Shared IPs (common on budget email platforms) mean other senders' poor behavior impacts your deliverability. Dedicated IPs give you full control but only make sense at 50,000+ monthly sends.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">
              <span class="faq-q-text">What bounce rate damages sender reputation?</span>
              <span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Keep hard bounce rates below 0.5%. Exceeding this signals to ISPs that your list quality is poor, which triggers filtering and can escalate to blacklisting.</p></div></div>
          </div>
